qualityReport.preamble:
This report contains all the subreports applicable to the
 quality of a VASP calculation, with a summary at the end.

_storage.name: kintegration
_storage.report,text:
The k-space integration was carried out over
 a 10 x 10 x 10 mesh of points in reciprocal space, using
 first-order Methfessel-Paxton smearing with a width of 0.2 eV. This k-mesh corresponds to spacings of
 0.025 x 0.025 x 0.025 1/Ang. For more information on
 the k-spacing see http://cms.mpi.univie.ac.at/vasp/vasp/KSPACING_tag_KGAMMA_tag.html.

Warning: The k-mesh is probably not large enough
 for this  metallic system. A k-spacing of 0.020 1/Ang or smaller is
 recommended.

See http://cms.mpi.univie.ac.at/vasp/vasp/ISMEAR_SIGMA_FERWE_FERDO_SMEARINGS_tag.html for more information.
_storage.title: k-point integration

_storage.name: material_type
_storage.report,text:
This system is a bulk material.
 The material is a metal, based on the 10 x 10 x 10
 k-mesh used in the calculation. The k-mesh has 7 or more points in all periodic directions, which means that the analysis of the type of material is almost certainly reliable.

For more information on metals see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metal.
_storage.title: Material type

_storage.name: minimum_setup
_storage.report,text:
The INCAR file does not define keywords 'ENCUT'.
 It is recommmended that you always define 'PREC', 'ENCUT',
 'LREAL', and 'ISMEAR' in the INCAR file.

For more information, see https://cms.mpi.univie.ac.at/vasp/vasp/Recommended_minimum_setup.html
_storage.title: Recommended minimum setup

_storage.name: potentials
_storage.report,text:
The potentials noted in the OUTCAR file appear to be
 those distributed with VASP:
nobreak
	PAW_PBE Al 04Jan2001 is from PAW_PBE_52/Al/POTCAR
_storage.title: Potentials

_storage.name: structure_optimization
_storage.preamble: Stucture optimization using the conjugate-gradients method, optimizing the atom positions and cell.

_storage.name: structure optimization/convergence
_storage.report,text:
The optimization converged to a difference of 0.0000100 eV between steps in 3 steps.

However, you are using the change in energy as the
 convergence criterion. It is suggested to use the
 forces (negative EDIFFG) since the change in energy
 is not a reliable indication of convergence.
_storage.title: Convergence

_storage.name: structure optimization/encut
_storage.report,text:
The value of ENCUT (240.3) is less than 30% larger than
 the largest ENMAX (240.3) of the potentials. This is
 typically not good enough for an accurate optimized
 structure. You might want to either use accurate
 precision (PREC = ACCURATE) or increase ENCUT to 312.4
 in the INCAR file!

For more information, see https://cms.mpi.univie.ac.at/vasp/vasp/PREC_tag.html.
 You might also wish to add 'ADDGRID = .TRUE.'. See
 https://cms.mpi.univie.ac.at/vasp/vasp/PAW_control_tags.html for more information.
_storage.title: Planewave cutoff (ENCUT)

_storage.name: structure optimization/drift
_storage.report,text:
The drift in the forces is small: 0.0000 0.0000 0.0000,
 The energy was used as the convergence criterion for the
 optimization, so it is hard to relate to the forces;
 however, the optimization, if converged, will
 probably predict the atom positions accurately.

See http://cms.mpi.univie.ac.at/vasp/guide/node170.html for more information about the drift force.
_storage.title: 'Drift' of forces

_storage.name: structure optimization/volume
_storage.report,text:
The lattice changed by 0.1%. Since the planewave basis is
 fixed during a run, if the cell changes too much, you should
 restart the optimization to refresh the basis. With this
 small change in the cell, there is no need for another run.

See https://cms.mpi.univie.ac.at/vasp/vasp/Accurate_bulk_relaxations_with_internal_parameters_one.html for more information.
_storage.title: Volume change
Structure optimization
